    "dcterms:abstract": [
        {
            "@language": "ja",
            "@value": "人間が人間を差別することの愚かしさ、悲しさ、恐ろしさ･･･奴隷制や人種差別への反対を貫いた『アンクル・トムの小屋』の作者ストウ夫人は、遂にその朗読会を最後にしようと決め、なぜこの小説を書くに至ったか話し始めます。子育てに追われながらも幸せに暮らしていた頃のある悲しい出来事が、その後、彼女自身を奴隷解放運動へと導くのですが、その出来事とは･･･彼女が朗読する小説の一節は、そのまま劇中劇として上演さします。",
            "is_public": true,
            "property_id": 19,
            "property_label": "Abstract",
            "type": "literal"
        },
        {
            "@language": "en",
            "@value": "The foolishness, the sadness, and the horror of people discriminating against people… Mrs. Stowe, the author of a novel “Uncle Tom’s Cabin” that opposes slavery and racism, finally decided to make this reading the last, and begins to talk about why she wrote this novel.\r\n A sad incident, which occurred when she was still living happily with her children, led her to the abolitionist movement. \r\n What was the incident…? A passage in the novel she reads is performed as a play within the play.",
            "is_public": true,
            "property_id": 19,
            "property_label": "Abstract",
            "type": "literal"
        }
    ],
